observations/codex/2026-05-25-originality-as-product.md:13:If the system optimizes for corpus size, it will become a summarizer. If it optimizes for novelty alone, it will become speculative. The useful target is disciplined originality: new ideas that survive source grounding, cross-tradition comparison, and adversarial critique.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:23:It is not yet a doctrine. It is the felt or conceptual pressure that appears after negation. Different traditions then manage that pressure differently.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:31:Another may bracket it: the pressure is a reportable feature of practice, but it does not settle metaphysics.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:49:- Does this source acknowledge pressure after negation?
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:53:- Does it explain it through mind, body, or attention?
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:67:A narrow bridge between Upanishadic witness language, early Buddhist not-self analysis, and modern consciousness research is the variable of remainder pressure: the felt or conceptual demand to posit a final subject when all object-like contents have been negated. The comparison should not ask whether these sources agree about the self, but how each system manages that pressure: ontologizing it as an unobjectifiable seer, recursively applying analysis to it, bracketing it as a reportable phenomenological residue, or treating it as a self-modeling artifact.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:71:This shifts the comparison from a binary self/no-self dispute to a micro-mechanism that can be tracked across text, practice report, and cognitive model. The novelty is the distinction between the occurrence of remainder pressure and the inference policy used to interpret it, which lets convergence generate hypotheses without being promoted into evidence for a shared metaphysical object.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:75:- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 as cited in observations/codex/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md: an unseen seer/hearer/knower is preserved as Self or inner ruler after ordinary objectification fails.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:76:- SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta as cited in observations/codex/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md: all five aggregates, including consciousness, are impermanent and not fit to regard as mine, I, or self.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:77:- observations/codex/2026-05-25-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation.md: compares traditions by whether negation licenses, tests, or refuses a proposed remainder.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:78:- observations/codex/2026-05-25-translation-strain-as-a-load-test-for-convergence.md and docs/original-idea-methodology.md: translation strain and claim decomposition should preserve the distinction between textual evidence, analogy, and speculation.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:83:The proposal may over-psychologize explicitly metaphysical or soteriological texts and may smuggle a modern cognitive-science frame into traditions that are not primarily explaining mental representation. It also depends on whether practitioners actually experience a comparable pressure after negation; without close philology, practice manuals, and first-person reports, the bridge could become an elegant label for a loose analogy.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:102:- practice_testability: 0.68
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:104:- source_reliability: 0.67
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:109:- Define a four-part remainder-pressure rubric: phenomenological residue, inference authorization, practice instruction, and metaphysical upgrade.
